<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7727ba86-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s284b"><num value="284b">§ 284b.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There are authorized to be appropriated such sums as may be necessary, but not in excess of $5,473,000, to carry out the purposes of this subchapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7727ba87-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/671/s3">Pub. L. 89–671, § 3</ref>, <date date="1966-10-15">Oct. 15, 1966</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/80/951">80 Stat. 951</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/92/272/tII/s201/4">Pub. L. 92–272, title II, § 201(4)</ref>, <date date="1972-04-11">Apr. 11, 1972</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/86/120">86 Stat. 120</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7727ba88-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id7727ba89-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id7727ba8a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1972—<ref href="/us/pl/92/272">Pub. L. 92–272</ref> increased maximum sums authorized to be appropriated from not in excess of $600,000 to not in excess of $5,473,000.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
